                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>At the 206th meeting of the National Security Council, July 15, in Washington,
                    the Council devoted a substantial amount of time to a report by the Secretary of
                    State on his talks in Paris with Premier <persName corresp="#p_MFP1"
                        >Mendès-France</persName> and Foreign Secretary <persName corresp="#p_EA1"
                        >Eden</persName> and to the decision that Under Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_SWB1">Smith</persName> would return to the Geneva Conference as
                    Head of the United States Delegation.</p>
                <p>For a memorandum of discussion of this meeting, see <ref
                        target="frus1952-54v13p1">volume XIII</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
